<div class="wrapper wrapper-content animated slideInRight">
  <div class="jumbotron text-center">
    <h2><%= gettext "Welcome to %{name}", name: "Flexcility!" %></h2>
    <p class="lead text-center">The facility management system for<br />everyone, everywhere, everytime.</p>
  </div>

<section class="container features">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-3 text-center wow fadeInLeft">
      <h1>Projects</h1>
      <p>Projects are the main division that comprises of a facility such as a building or group of buildings.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-6 text-center">
      <div class="navy-line"></div>
      <h2>Finally, a facility management system at your fingertips<br/><span class="navy"?>designed for accessibility, ease of use, comprehensive audit trail, transparency and effective delivery</span></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-3 text-center wow fadeInRight">
      <h1>Assets</h1>
      <p>Assets are grouped items which are part of a particular project.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="container services">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-4 text-center">
      <h1>Work Requests</h1>
      <p>A work request is generated by anyone, typically end users, upon identification of assets that require maintenance, repair, or replacement. A work request id is generated and is used in reference for all documentation and actions that result from it.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-4 text-center">
      <h1>Work Orders</h1>
      <p>A work order is raised from a work request by the administration, typically the management team of a particular project, depending on their evaluation of the work request with the option of consultation with appropriate qualified personal, which is then distributed to registered technicians for eventual assignment to the work order.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-4 text-center">
      <h1>Work Reports</h1>
      <p>Once a work order has been carried out by the assigned technician, a work report is generated by the technician to the satisfaction of the work request owner before being submitted to the administration for approval and  closeout.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-lg-4">
  </div>
  <div class="col-lg-4 features-text text-center">
    <div class="navy-line"></div>
    <h1>Customizable Workflow</h1>
    <p>Flexcility provides a basic workflow derived from industry best practices with the goal of enabling quick and efficient response for proper and robust facility management. Customizable workflow can be obtained via workflow customization options within the app. For more complex workflow, customization packages are available to suit your needs.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-lg-4">
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-lg-12"><center><img src="<%= static_path(@conn, "/images/flex-flowchart-02alpha.png") %>" alt="flex-flowchart" class="img-responsive" width="250px" align="middle">
  </center></div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="col-lg-12 text-center">
<a href="" class="btn btn-default">Learn More</a>
